## Conceptual Summary
Contradiction Theory explains cognition as a **system of interacting gradients**.  
It integrates:
- gradient opposition (structure)  
- contradiction dynamics (behavior)  
- contradiction failure modes (breakdown)  
- contradiction repair (restoration)  

Together, these documents form a complete model of how cognitive tension emerges, destabilizes, and resolves.

---

## Relationship to Other HERMES Modules
Contradiction Theory connects directly to:
- **Field Dynamics** (gradient opposition, turbulence, failure modes)  
- **Recursion Theory** (recursive amplification of contradictions)  
- **Identity Stabilization Theory** (identity conflict, fragmentation)  
- **Awareness Gradient Theory** (visibility of contradictions)  
- **HERMES Runtime** (INVERT, HARMONIZE, PERTURB operators)  

It is one of the core structural layers of the unified cognitive architecture.

